Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips then halve widthways. Pop the aubergine and pepper onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then sprinkle over the @ground cumin{1%tsp}. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then set aside.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. Once your oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Pop the aubergine and pepper on the middle shelf to roast until golden and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn both halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%can} in a #colander{}. Put half into a #bowl{} and mash with a #fork{} until broken up. Pick the @mint{1%sprig} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

While everything roasts, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @tomato puree{30%g} and the garlic. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{100%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, mixed beans (both whole and crushed) and the @harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you don't like heat). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} into a small bowl and add the mint. Season to taste, stir together and set aside. Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} into small pieces. Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} in the oven to warm through for the last ~{2%minutes} of roasting time. Once the beans are cooked, taste and season again if needed. TIP: Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Spread a dollop of yoghurt over the base of each tortilla. Top with spoonfuls of the harissa beans, aubergine, peppers and feta. TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in! Serve the wedges and any remaining yoghurt alongside for dipping. Enjoy!